OL,6,FHe continued that the boy "is a unique
OL,7,Fchild who would not exist but for the
OL,8,Funusual arrangements made for his
OL,9,Fconception, but those arrangements
OL,10,Fhave also created the potential for
OL,11,Fhim to suffer emotional harm were he
OL,12,Fto learn of them".
OL,14,FJustice Poole said the man had an
OL,15,Festablished father-and-son
OL,16,Frelationship with the child and it was
OL,17,Fup to him and the boy's mother to
OL,18,F"manage the latent risks to his
OL,19,Fwelfare".
